diagnoses_procedures_extraction.template:
Extract DIAGNOSES and PROCEDURES from the following medical record context.

IMPORTANT: Pay close attention to dates!

{context}

CRITICAL: You MUST return a JSON OBJECT with this EXACT structure:

{
  "diagnoses": [
    {
      "name": "diagnosis name",
      "icd_code": "ICD code or null",
      "type": "primary/secondary/admitting/discharge",
      "date": "MM/DD/YYYY or null",
      "status": "active/resolved/chronic"
    }
  ],
  "procedures": [
    {
      "name": "procedure name",
      "date": "MM/DD/YYYY or null",
      "provider": "performing provider or null",
      "location": "where performed or null",
      "findings": "results/findings or null",
      "complications": "complications or null"
    }
  ]
}

CRITICAL INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Extract dates! Convert to MM/DD/YYYY format.
2. Include ALL items mentioned.
3. Return ONLY valid JSON. Do not include any text before or after the JSON object.

timeline_extraction.template:
Extract any additional temporal events from this medical text that aren't already captured in structured extraction. Look for key clinical events with dates.

Medical Text:
{text}

Return a JSON object with this structure:
{
  "events": [
    {
      "date": "MM/DD/YYYY",
      "event_type": "Admission/Discharge/Procedure/Note/etc",
      "description": "Detailed description of the event"
    }
  ]
}

Return ONLY valid JSON.

gap_detection.template:
Analyze the extracted clinical data for referential gaps.
Look for:
1. Medications mentioned without a confirmed diagnosis or indication.
2. Imaging studies referenced in history but not found in the 'Imaging' list.
3. Inconsistencies in dates (e.g., surgery after the request date).
4. Missing duration for treatments like PT or OT.

CLINICAL DATA:
- Diagnoses: {diagnoses}
- Medications: {medications}
- Imaging: {imaging}

Return a JSON object:
{
  "gaps": [
    {
      "title": "Short descriptive title",
      "reason": "Neutral explanation of the gap",
      "source_file": "File name if applicable",
      "source_page": page_number_if_applicable
    }
  ]
}
